Received a suspicious email or message? Don’t rush to click!  Phishing scams can cost everything if you're not careful. Always double-check links before taking action! 

Common Tricks to Watch Out For: 
1️⃣ Fake “Official Notices”:  “Your account will be suspended soon, verify now!”  Phishing link: https://kuco1n-support(dot)com (Looks legit, but it’s fake!) 
✅ Safe tip: Always verify links and only trust the official KuCoin site: https://www.kucoin.com. Do not click suspicious links or enter personal information on fake websites! 

2️⃣ “Limited-Time Rewards” Scams:  “Congratulations! You’ve won 100 USDT. Click to claim!”  Phishing link: https://kucoin-airdrop(dot)io 
✅ KuCoin rewards are always distributed directly to your account. We will never send links via private messages or ask for your private keys or passwords to claim rewards.  

💡 One wrong click can cost everything—stay alert and stay safe!

🔒 KuCoin Security Sunday Tip: Beware of Public Wi-Fi!

☕️✈️ Connecting to public Wi-Fi at cafés, airports, hotels, or other shared spaces might seem convenient—but it comes with serious risks. Hackers can easily launch man-in-the-middle (MITM) attacks to intercept your data, putting your passwords, private keys, and personal information at risk.

Stay Safe While Trading on the Go:
1️⃣ Avoid Logging into Exchanges on Public Wi-Fi
Public networks are often unsecured. Avoid using networks with suspicious names like “Free WiFi” or those without passwords.
2️⃣ Use a VPN (Virtual Private Network)
A VPN encrypts your internet traffic, keeping your data private even on public connections.
3️⃣ Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
Add an extra layer of protection to your account using Google Authenticator, SMS codes, or a hardware key.

📌 Pro Tip: If you must trade while on the move, use the KuCoin mobile app with biometric security (like fingerprint or facial recognition) for enhanced protection.
Just a casual reminder that we’re still early.
